==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chicory
<hw>Chic"o*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>chicor⟦eacute⟧e</ets>, earlier also <ets>cichor⟦eacute⟧e</ets>, L.
<ets>cichorium</ets>, fr. Gr. <ets><?/</ets>, <ets><?/</ets>,
<ets>Cf</ets>. <er>Succory</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A branching perennial plant (<spn>Cichorium Intybus</spn>) with
bright blue flowers, growing wild in Europe, Asia, and America; also
cultivated for its roots and as a salad plant; succory; wild endive. See
<er>Endive</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The root, which is roasted for mixing with
coffee.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>chicot</ent>⟦br⟧
